Fix use-after-free in NodeApiFinalizerHolder::invokeAllFinalizers().

The loop `while (!finalizers_.empty())` relies on invokeFinalizerFromGC()
removing the reference from this holder's set. But it only unlinks via the
reference's own finalizerHolder_ backlink, which for external-buffer finalizers
(created with no JS value -> null backlink, added to a temporary holder in
~NodeApiExternalBuffer via addFinalizer() without setting a backlink) does NOT
point at this temporary holder. invokeFinalizerFromGC() also deletes the
reference (kRuntime ownership). The freed pointer therefore stays in the set and
the next iteration dereferences it (null vtable -> SIGSEGV) -- reproducible by
GC-collecting an external ArrayBuffer then tearing down (js-native-api
test_typedarray under full env teardown). Erase the element before invoking so
the loop always makes progress regardless of backlink state.
diff --git a/API/hermes_node_api/hermes_node_api.cpp b/API/hermes_node_api/hermes_node_api.cpp
--- a/API/hermes_node_api/hermes_node_api.cpp
+++ b/API/hermes_node_api/hermes_node_api.cpp
@@ -2255,9 +2255,17 @@
 
 void NodeApiFinalizerHolder::invokeAllFinalizers() noexcept {
   while (!finalizers_.empty()) {
-    const auto &ref = finalizers_.begin();
-    (*ref)->invokeFinalizerFromGC(); // Delegates to NodeApiEnvironment for API
-                                     // version-dependent handling
+    // Remove the reference from this holder BEFORE invoking it. The loop relies
+    // on the set shrinking; invokeFinalizerFromGC() only unlinks via the
+    // reference's own finalizerHolder_ backlink, which for external-buffer
+    // finalizers (no JS value -> null backlink, added here via addFinalizer
+    // without a backlink) does NOT point at this temporary holder. It also may
+    // delete the reference (kRuntime ownership). Without erasing here the next
+    // iteration would re-read a freed pointer from finalizers_ (use-after-free).
+    NodeApiReference *ref = *finalizers_.begin();
+    finalizers_.erase(finalizers_.begin());
+    ref->invokeFinalizerFromGC(); // Delegates to NodeApiEnvironment for API
+                                  // version-dependent handling
   }
 }
 
